---
/**
 * ArchitectureDiagram — a vertical pipeline diagram of the "Global Textbooks
 * Operating Environment": a bounded outer container holding the Resources
 * Library, the IDEMS Middleware with its three parts, the Publishing Hub, and
 * locally-owned Local Variants, joined by bidirectional connectors.
 *
 * Content is hardcoded for now (some copy is still placeholder/TBD). Styling is
 * driven entirely by the global design tokens, so it reads as part of the site
 * rather than an embedded graphic. Decorative arrows are aria-hidden; the text
 * is read in pipeline order by assistive tech, and the whole thing is a
 * <figure> with the summary line as its <figcaption>.
 */
---

<figure class="oe">
  <span class="oe__label">Global Textbooks Operating Environment — Bounded</span>

  <div class="oe__node">
    <p class="oe__node-title">Resources Library</p>
    <p class="oe__node-desc">Open textbooks, resources and software; not yet structured for adaptation</p>
  </div>

  <div class="oe__connector">
    <span class="oe__arrow oe__arrow--up" aria-hidden="true"></span>
    <span class="oe__connector-label">[[HIGH-QUALITY FOUNDATIONS OF ADAPTATION]</span>
    <span class="oe__arrow oe__arrow--down" aria-hidden="true"></span>
  </div>

  <div class="oe__middleware">
    <div class="oe__middleware-head">
      <p class="oe__middleware-title">IDEMS Middleware</p>
      <p class="oe__middleware-subhead">Systemic Meaning-Making</p>
    </div>

    <div class="oe__part">
      <p class="oe__part-title">IDEMS IP</p>
      <p class="oe__part-desc">
        IDEMS’ core innovation: Resources Library content, and the complex knowledge about how data must be combined for impact, are transformed into structured data in a unified semantic system.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="oe__connector oe__connector--tight">
      <span class="oe__arrow oe__arrow--down" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      <span class="oe__connector-label oe__connector-label--muted">structures into</span>
    </div>

    <div class="oe__part">
      <p class="oe__part-title">Textbooks Brain</p>
      <p class="oe__part-desc">
        Building out of IDEMS’ IP, the Brain holds the newly structured Resource Library data in a novel deterministic core. This expert-maintained core is the foundation of responsible, auditable AI that helps educators and authors make sense of the Brain’s structured, malleable data and easily create new textbook adaptations and versions.

      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="oe__connector oe__connector--tight">
      <span class="oe__arrow oe__arrow--down" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      <span class="oe__connector-label oe__connector-label--muted">trains</span>
    </div>

    <div class="oe__part">
      <p class="oe__part-title">Agentic AI Hands</p>
      <p class="oe__part-desc">
        Developed for narrow use cases, this suite of expert AI agents support textbook publishing, adaptation and iteration by non-technologist educators and authors.  Trained on the Textbooks Brain’s high-quality data, AI Hands are bounded, auditable, and resource efficient. 
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="oe__connector">
    <span class="oe__arrow oe__arrow--up" aria-hidden="true"></span>
    <span class="oe__connector-label">[ADAPTATION & LOCALISATION]</span>
    <span class="oe__arrow oe__arrow--down" aria-hidden="true"></span>
  </div>

  <div class="oe__node">
    <p class="oe__node-title">Customisation & Publishing Hub</p>
    <p class="oe__node-desc">Educators create &amp; publish with trained Agentic AI Hands</p>
  </div>

  <div class="oe__connector">
    <span class="oe__arrow oe__arrow--up" aria-hidden="true"></span>
    <span class="oe__arrow oe__arrow--down" aria-hidden="true"></span>
  </div>

  <div class="oe__node oe__node--dashed">
    <p class="oe__node-title">Local Variants</p>
    <p class="oe__node-desc">Unlimited, owned locally</p>
  </div>

  <figcaption class="oe__caption">
    Every arrow runs both ways — local adaptation flows back upstream,
    continuously structuring and improving the Brain and the Library it draws
    from.
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  /* Bounded outer container: the whole operating environment. A firm (solid)
     1px border reads as the "bounded" edge; the label chip straddles it. */
  .oe {
    max-width: 40rem;
    margin-inline: auto;
    position: relative;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    padding: var(--space-5);
    border: 2px solid var(--color-border-strong);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
  }

  /* Framing label, sitting on the top border as a small accent pill (echoes
     the section eyebrow-badge treatment). */
  .oe__label {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: var(--space-4);
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-3);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: var(--color-bg);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  /* Top-level nodes (Resources Library, Publishing Hub, Local Variants): white
     cards that lift off the tinted container. */
  .oe__node {
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    border: var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    background: var(--color-bg);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .oe__node--dashed {
    border-style: dashed;
    border-color: var(--color-border-strong);
  }
  .oe__node-title {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .oe__node-desc {
    margin-top: var(--space-1);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  /* Bidirectional connectors: outward-pointing arrowheads with an optional
     label between them. The arrowheads are CSS triangles, no SVG needed. */
  .oe__connector {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-1);
    padding-block: var(--space-2);
  }
  .oe__connector--tight {
    padding-block: var(--space-1);
  }
  .oe__arrow {
    width: 0;
    height: 0;
    border-inline: 5px solid transparent;
  }
  .oe__arrow--up {
    border-bottom: 6px solid var(--color-text-subtle);
  }
  .oe__arrow--down {
    border-top: 6px solid var(--color-text-subtle);
  }
  .oe__connector-label {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-align: center;
  }
  /* Internal transforms ("structures into", "trains"): quieter than the
     boundary-crossing labels — muted, lower-case, italic. */
  .oe__connector-label--muted {
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: normal;
    text-transform: none;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  /* IDEMS Middleware panel — the pioneering core. A solid accent border plus a
     faint accent tint set it apart as the special layer (the tint falls back to
     the plain surface where color-mix isn't supported). */
  .oe__middleware {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    padding: var(--space-4);
    border: 1.5px dashed var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 6%, var(--color-bg));
  }
  .oe__middleware-head {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .oe__middleware-title {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .oe__middleware-subhead {
    margin-top: var(--space-1);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  /* IP / Brain / Hands cards inside the middleware. */
  .oe__part {
    padding: var(--space-4);
    border: var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    background: var(--color-bg);
  }
  .oe__part-title {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .oe__part-desc {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }
  .oe__part-desc em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
  }

  .oe__caption {
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    text-align: center;
  }
</style>
